Herr Schopenhauer says:
&ldquo;we are only that one eye of the world which looks out from all knowing creatures&hellip;&rdquo;
mudgala bhArmyashva says:
&ldquo;tvaM vishvasya jagatash chakShur indrAsi chakShuShaH |&rdquo;
You O indra, are the [eye] of the entire universe, the eye of the eye.
While it is well known that Schopenhauer was influenced by H ideas, AFAIK he was not well-conversant with the RV. So this expression might be seen as convergent.
